I would like to draw your attention to the slide,

00:42:17.000 --> 00:42:21.000
where, as an example, the competence of working with clients is given,

00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:26.000
and the methods of assessment that the company has in stock are listed.

00:42:26.000 --> 00:42:28.000
This is from the filling of the assessment sheet,

00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:30.000
the method is 360 degrees,

00:42:30.000 --> 00:42:34.000
and as we see that instead of the subordinate, the client participates here,

00:42:34.000 --> 00:42:36.000
assesses the employee.

00:42:36.000 --> 00:42:40.000
This can be a written assessment of the knowledge of the assortment and the work technique,

00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:43.000
work with clients, that is, an assessment of knowledge.

00:42:43.000 --> 00:42:48.000
This is a business game that is developed based on the situation that took place.

00:42:48.000 --> 00:42:52.000
And also this is a case that is offered to the participants to decide.

00:42:52.000 --> 00:42:59.000
Again, someone else for this competence can offer some other methods.

00:42:59.000 --> 00:43:03.000
Maybe there will be only two of them, maybe three, they will be completely different.

00:43:03.000 --> 00:43:07.000
In this case, in this example, we see a choice of a specific company.

00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:12.000
When the staff understands that in order to assess the competence of working with our employees,

00:43:12.000 --> 00:43:16.000
these methods are available.

00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:20.000
So, we have assessed our employees.

00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:25.000
We have laid out the required level of development or profile of the position on our axes,

00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:31.000
on which we have laid out the competence, drew webs,

00:43:31.000 --> 00:43:36.000
and then applied the current level of development of our employees' competences.

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:41.000
We receive information for analysis, and we need to use this information.

00:43:41.000 --> 00:43:44.000
How can we use it?

00:43:44.000 --> 00:43:49.000
We can either make an individual plan and programs for each employee.

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:56.000
We determine which employees we will represent in the personnel reserve.

00:43:56.000 --> 00:44:02.000
Speaking of the personnel reserve, it is important to understand that if we define this group for ourselves,

00:44:02.000 --> 00:44:06.000
the group can be very large, or the positions can be different.

00:44:06.000 --> 00:44:09.000
This does not mean that we have presented the whole group in the reserve for all positions.

00:44:09.000 --> 00:44:10.000
Absolutely not.

00:44:10.000 --> 00:44:15.000
We remember that in order to be listed in the personnel reserve and for subsequent development,

00:44:15.000 --> 00:44:22.000
it is necessary to assess, or to impose the assessment that we have made,

00:44:22.000 --> 00:44:28.000
but already to impose on the competence profile the position under which we select the reserve.

00:44:28.000 --> 00:44:32.000
This does not mean that everything is again, everything is from the beginning.

00:44:32.000 --> 00:44:42.000
If we represent an employee in the reserve, in the higher position,

00:44:42.000 --> 00:44:45.000
then these are positions within the same group of positions.

00:44:45.000 --> 00:44:50.000
Therefore, there will be the same corporate competences, the same professional competences.

00:44:50.000 --> 00:44:54.000
The only thing that can be added is management competences,

00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:59.000
if the employee did not engage in management activities in the previous position.

00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:06.000
Thus, we can or plan to list the people we are listing in the personnel reserve.

00:45:06.000 --> 00:45:10.000
We propose to give them another exercise,

00:45:10.000 --> 00:45:16.000
within which we will observe the level of development of their management competences for subsequent assessment.

00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:19.000
The next is the planning of the employee's career.

00:45:19.000 --> 00:45:25.000
This is an opportunity that we have, and we can understand and give the employee feedback

00:45:25.000 --> 00:45:28.000
so that he understands what he can expect while working in our company.

00:45:28.000 --> 00:45:31.000
The next is the adjustment of compensation packages.

00:45:31.000 --> 00:45:35.000
I say this because the word adjustment is very soft,

00:45:35.000 --> 00:45:38.000
it is by no means a change in compensation packages.

00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:39.000
What does it mean?

00:45:39.000 --> 00:45:44.000
I do not recommend you to change the labor payment system,

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:49.000
to increase the salary based on the results of the assessment on competences,

00:45:49.000 --> 00:45:54.000
because we pay for the result, and competences are still behavior.

00:45:55.000 --> 00:46:00.000
We should not pay for the behavior demonstrated, no matter how it sounds.

00:46:00.000 --> 00:46:07.000
It is clear that if the assessment on competences coincides with the assessment on activity,

00:46:07.000 --> 00:46:09.000
then it can be the next step.

00:46:09.000 --> 00:46:17.000
In any case, be careful, remember that only for the results of the assessment center,

00:46:17.000 --> 00:46:20.000
compensation packages should not be changed easily.

00:46:20.000 --> 00:46:22.000
There should be another reason for this.

00:46:22.000 --> 00:46:26.000
Let's talk about the use of competences in the development of the staff.

00:46:26.000 --> 00:46:33.000
We did a lot of work, we evaluated, and we understand that there is a group of employees

00:46:33.000 --> 00:46:37.000
with a number of competences that we need to improve.

00:46:37.000 --> 00:46:40.000
We all together, it is clear that they need to be improved,

00:46:40.000 --> 00:46:45.000
but we, if we are a staff service, need to create an environment

00:46:45.000 --> 00:46:49.000
and provide the tools that will help employees do this.

00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:54.000
First of all, we develop special training programs,

00:46:54.000 --> 00:46:58.000
whether individual or group, for the development of competences.

00:46:58.000 --> 00:47:03.000
We can do this within our training centers, or within the company,

00:47:03.000 --> 00:47:09.000
or we can attract external partners to achieve these goals.

00:47:09.000 --> 00:47:12.000
There are many methods of training, they are different.

00:47:12.000 --> 00:47:17.000
They are different in quality, they are different in duration, they are different in cost.

00:47:18.000 --> 00:47:22.000
Again, from these methods, we choose those that are acceptable

00:47:22.000 --> 00:47:27.000
for the development of specific competences of specific employees in our companies.

00:47:27.000 --> 00:47:32.000
Thus, we will get the so-called development action menu,

00:47:32.000 --> 00:47:35.000
or individual development plans.

00:47:35.000 --> 00:47:41.000
When for the development of a certain competence, we have certain methods.

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:44.000
Remember, we had an assessment matrix there.

00:47:44.000 --> 00:47:46.000
How can we assess competences?

00:47:46.000 --> 00:47:51.000
The same thing here, the matrix of development actions.

00:47:51.000 --> 00:47:53.000
How can we develop this competence?

00:47:53.000 --> 00:47:55.000
What methods do we have?

00:47:55.000 --> 00:47:58.000
The methods can be completely different.

00:47:58.000 --> 00:48:02.000
It can be self-learning, it can be mentorship,

00:48:02.000 --> 00:48:05.000
as one of the most effective methods.

00:48:05.000 --> 00:48:08.000
It can be participation in development projects,

00:48:08.000 --> 00:48:12.000
training and seminar.

00:48:12.000 --> 00:48:18.000
It can be participation or even holding some master classes,

00:48:18.000 --> 00:48:21.000
most likely inside the company.

00:48:21.000 --> 00:48:24.000
It's not that we send an employee to train someone.

00:48:24.000 --> 00:48:30.000
But we say that if he has some professional knowledge,

00:48:30.000 --> 00:48:35.000
and on the other hand, he needs to develop competences related to communication,

00:48:35.000 --> 00:48:39.000
work, let's say, a speech in front of an audience, and so on,

00:48:39.000 --> 00:48:43.000
why not share his knowledge in this format?

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:45.000
It can be a development center.

00:48:45.000 --> 00:48:49.000
We talked about assessment centers.

00:48:49.000 --> 00:48:53.000
But there is also such a concept as a development center.

00:48:53.000 --> 00:48:58.000
The point is that the algorithm of conduct is similar,

00:48:58.000 --> 00:49:00.000
as we said about the assessment center,

00:49:00.000 --> 00:49:01.000
but the goal is different.

00:49:01.000 --> 00:49:08.000
The goal is not to assess, but to train during its implementation.

00:49:08.000 --> 00:49:11.000
When an employee performs an exercise,

00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:14.000
he immediately receives feedback.

00:49:14.000 --> 00:49:17.000
And then, within the framework of the development center,

00:49:17.000 --> 00:49:21.000
he receives another exercise and an opportunity to demonstrate and improve his skills.

00:49:21.000 --> 00:49:24.000
The goal is not just to collect some information,

00:49:24.000 --> 00:49:29.000
but to let the employee try to change his behavior

00:49:29.000 --> 00:49:34.000
taking into account the feedback he received from the observers.

00:49:34.000 --> 00:49:37.000
It is important to remember that employees with high grades,

00:49:37.000 --> 00:49:41.000
that is, with a high level of competence, regardless of their position,

00:49:41.000 --> 00:49:47.000
can and should perform as functional coaches and mentors.

00:49:47.000 --> 00:49:50.000
Moreover, this is a great advantage for the company

00:49:50.000 --> 00:49:56.000
when the most valuable knowledge can be passed from one employee to another.

00:49:56.000 --> 00:49:58.000
This is also a plus for the employee, a kind of advantage,

00:49:58.000 --> 00:50:02.000
because it is related to his inner motivation,

00:50:02.000 --> 00:50:06.000
including the fact that he becomes an internal or functional coach.

00:50:06.000 --> 00:50:10.000
Not to mention that if the company has a mentor motivation system,

00:50:10.000 --> 00:50:16.000
it will always be an additional benefit.

00:50:16.000 --> 00:50:19.000
Speaking of competence development,

00:50:19.000 --> 00:50:24.000
we cannot help but talk about the competencies that are difficult to develop.

00:50:24.000 --> 00:50:27.000
Some people call them undeveloped competencies,

00:50:27.000 --> 00:50:30.000
but this name probably has a certain predisposition,

00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:32.000
because if we call it competence,

00:50:32.000 --> 00:50:36.000
we must accept that what has grown has grown.

00:50:36.000 --> 00:50:39.000
What level of competence does the employee have?

00:50:39.000 --> 00:50:41.000
We should always work with this.

00:50:41.000 --> 00:50:43.000
Of course, there is a part of irony in this,

00:50:43.000 --> 00:50:47.000
because undeveloped competencies are those competencies

00:50:47.000 --> 00:50:51.000
within which it is quite difficult to change a person.

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:56.000
Nevertheless, we must understand whether such competencies exist in our model.

00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:58.000
Loyalty.

00:50:58.000 --> 00:51:01.000
How can we evaluate it?

00:51:01.000 --> 00:51:03.000
How will we develop it?

00:51:03.000 --> 00:51:07.000
How will we tell a person to be loyal if we want him to behave like this?

00:51:07.000 --> 00:51:09.000
It's not that simple.

00:51:09.000 --> 00:51:11.000
Such competencies can be different.

00:51:11.000 --> 00:51:13.000
For example, the competence of creativity.

00:51:13.000 --> 00:51:16.000
Competencies are not often found.

00:51:16.000 --> 00:51:19.000
It can be either in some small creative organizations,

00:51:19.000 --> 00:51:23.000
or it can be a professional competence of some group of employees.

00:51:23.000 --> 00:51:27.000
Nevertheless, at the stage of formulating competence,

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:29.000
remembering and answering the question

00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:33.000
how we can analyze and whether we can develop this competence in the future,

00:51:33.000 --> 00:51:36.000
it is worth thinking about it in some way.

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:41.000
And, accordingly, later just understand that this is one of such competencies.

00:51:41.000 --> 00:51:44.000
Therefore, what tools do we have?

00:51:44.000 --> 00:51:50.000
The first is to analyze and select people at the entrance to the company for these competencies.

00:51:50.000 --> 00:51:55.000
That is, not to miss people who do not have the level that we need

00:51:55.000 --> 00:51:57.000
if this competence is a priority.

00:51:57.000 --> 00:52:00.000
Also, develop a system of stimulation.

00:52:00.000 --> 00:52:04.000
If we use not only development tools,

00:52:04.000 --> 00:52:06.000
but tools from another field,

00:52:06.000 --> 00:52:09.000
that is, the behavior that we think is necessary.

00:52:09.000 --> 00:52:14.000
And also, again, try to determine the methods that may be.

00:52:14.000 --> 00:52:16.000
Among which there may be coaching,

00:52:16.000 --> 00:52:19.000
among which there must be feedback.

00:52:19.000 --> 00:52:23.000
If a person is interested in developing this competence,

00:52:23.000 --> 00:52:25.000
if he has an inner desire,

00:52:25.000 --> 00:52:27.000
then this method will be very effective,

00:52:27.000 --> 00:52:29.000
because he will receive feedback

00:52:29.000 --> 00:52:31.000
either from a colleague, from a manager,

00:52:31.000 --> 00:52:33.000
or from some internal expert.

00:52:33.000 --> 00:52:40.000
And he will change and consciously change his activity in the direction that is necessary.

00:52:40.000 --> 00:52:45.000
A few words about the personnel reserve, which we have already talked about today.

00:52:45.000 --> 00:52:49.000
First of all, it is necessary to determine for ourselves what we understand as a personnel reserve.

00:52:50.000 --> 00:52:56.000
Historically, we understand the personnel reserve as a reserve for a position,

00:52:56.000 --> 00:52:58.000
for any of the positions.

00:52:58.000 --> 00:53:01.000
It can be either a management reserve,

00:53:01.000 --> 00:53:04.000
that is, when specialists are formed,

00:53:04.000 --> 00:53:08.000
reservists are formed for the position of a manager,

00:53:08.000 --> 00:53:10.000
or from the manager of the lower link

00:53:10.000 --> 00:53:17.000
a reserve is formed for the position of a higher level manager.

00:53:17.000 --> 00:53:22.000
Nevertheless, there is a concept that has become part of our language today,

00:53:22.000 --> 00:53:25.000
which we read a lot in literature.

00:53:25.000 --> 00:53:27.000
This is the management of talents.

00:53:27.000 --> 00:53:30.000
When we form the so-called talent pool,

00:53:30.000 --> 00:53:32.000
what is it about?

00:53:32.000 --> 00:53:35.000
Is there any difference?

00:53:35.000 --> 00:53:38.000
Most often, those companies that adhere to this principle

00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:42.000
and say that we are not just forming a reserve for some position.

00:53:42.000 --> 00:53:47.000
No, we select talented specialists from different fields.

00:53:47.000 --> 00:53:51.000
We evaluate them, determining talent for ourselves in some way,

00:53:51.000 --> 00:53:54.000
and most often as a potential for development.

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:58.000
We already understand that this is a certain set of competencies.

00:53:58.000 --> 00:54:01.000
We determine these people for ourselves

00:54:01.000 --> 00:54:06.000
in order to pay more attention to them during our work with the personnel

00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:08.000
and understand that this is our future

00:54:08.000 --> 00:54:12.000
and that it is more convenient for us to invest in this particular category of employees.

00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:17.000
In this case, the talent pool is not for a specific position.

00:54:17.000 --> 00:54:21.000
There is no profile of the competence of the chief engineer,

00:54:21.000 --> 00:54:24.000
the reserve for which we are forming.

00:54:24.000 --> 00:54:27.000
There is a certain scope for the future,

00:54:27.000 --> 00:54:32.000
or a certain profile of success, as some companies call it.

00:54:32.000 --> 00:54:36.000
Thus, it is necessary to determine the direction in which we work.

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:39.000
Either we have a reserve for a position,

00:54:39.000 --> 00:54:41.000
or for a managerial position,

00:54:41.000 --> 00:54:44.000
or for a position of a specialist, a rare specialist,

00:54:44.000 --> 00:54:46.000
who is almost not on the market.

00:54:46.000 --> 00:54:50.000
Let's say a technologist in our tricky production.

00:54:50.000 --> 00:54:53.000
And we grow all technologists on our own.

00:54:53.000 --> 00:54:56.000
Or, once again, a talent pool.

00:54:56.000 --> 00:55:00.000
In any case, we understand that we select candidates

00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:04.000
for the pool and the reserve based on the results of evaluation events.

00:55:04.000 --> 00:55:07.000
We create individual development plans.

00:55:07.000 --> 00:55:11.000
Only if we understand what to include in the development plan,

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:14.000
because there is a profile of the position,

00:55:14.000 --> 00:55:17.000
in the reserve for which they are included,

00:55:17.000 --> 00:55:21.000
and we understand, comparing with their current profile of the position,

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:24.000
what competencies need to be developed.

00:55:24.000 --> 00:55:26.000
As for the talent pool,

00:55:26.000 --> 00:55:30.000
we are talking about a certain profile of success.

00:55:30.000 --> 00:55:33.000
When we set a certain level,

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:37.000
maybe we draw the profile of a young manager,

00:55:37.000 --> 00:55:41.000
or we define it for ourselves in some other way.

00:55:41.000 --> 00:55:44.000
And we start from this profile,

00:55:44.000 --> 00:55:47.000
which we have defined for ourselves.

00:55:50.000 --> 00:55:54.000
For reservists, individual plans are made.

00:55:54.000 --> 00:55:57.000
It is very important that people,

00:55:57.000 --> 00:56:01.000
who are listed in the reserve or in the talent pool,

00:56:01.000 --> 00:56:04.000
are not just listed once,

00:56:04.000 --> 00:56:07.000
but then, in a year, two or three,

00:56:07.000 --> 00:56:10.000
to see what happened to them.

00:56:10.000 --> 00:56:13.000
These are people, for whom we invest more money

00:56:13.000 --> 00:56:16.000
from the calculation for one employee than for other employees.

00:56:16.000 --> 00:56:20.000
Therefore, we need to constantly monitor the effectiveness of our investments.

00:56:20.000 --> 00:56:22.000
What does it mean?

00:56:22.000 --> 00:56:25.000
This is the level of reserve preparation.

00:56:25.000 --> 00:56:28.000
We gave recommendations to employees about what to do.

00:56:28.000 --> 00:56:31.000
Did any change happen or not?

00:56:31.000 --> 00:56:34.000
This is something that must be monitored.

00:56:34.000 --> 00:56:37.000
There are two aspects.

00:56:37.000 --> 00:56:42.000
The first is that our reserve group is very slow and fast.

00:56:42.000 --> 00:56:45.000
If our reserve is medium-term,

00:56:45.000 --> 00:56:48.000
for example, for three years,

00:56:48.000 --> 00:56:51.000
and we prepared it for a year,

00:56:51.000 --> 00:56:54.000
but in a year we do not need ready specialists in this area,

00:56:54.000 --> 00:56:57.000
what can happen?

00:56:57.000 --> 00:57:00.000
Everything can turn out great,

00:57:00.000 --> 00:57:03.000
the employee will say thank you,

00:57:03.000 --> 00:57:06.000
straighten his wings and continue his career in another organization.

00:57:06.000 --> 00:57:09.000
Therefore, you must feel this balance,

00:57:09.000 --> 00:57:12.000
initially programming the reserve period for which we are preparing.

00:57:12.000 --> 00:57:15.000
The benefits that the organization gets

00:57:15.000 --> 00:57:18.000
when forming and developing a personnel reserve cannot be overestimated.

00:57:18.000 --> 00:57:21.000
First of all, we must understand

00:57:21.000 --> 00:57:24.000
that this is a systematic and targeted development

00:57:24.000 --> 00:57:27.000
of a certain group of employees.

00:57:27.000 --> 00:57:30.000
The money is invested in the best.

00:57:30.000 --> 00:57:33.000
We do everything to maximize the return on these investments.

00:57:33.000 --> 00:57:36.000
The reservists themselves understand

00:57:36.000 --> 00:57:39.000
what the company expects from them

00:57:39.000 --> 00:57:42.000
if they have individual plans or plans for future careers.

00:57:42.000 --> 00:57:45.000
Thus, the best of them aim to develop

00:57:45.000 --> 00:57:48.000
in accordance with these expectations.

00:57:48.000 --> 00:57:51.000
Further, the corporate culture of the company

00:57:51.000 --> 00:57:54.000
is gradually changing.

00:57:54.000 --> 00:57:57.000
It becomes oriented towards personal development,

00:57:57.000 --> 00:58:00.000
initiative, creativity.

00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:03.000
In the hands of the line managers and the staff,

00:58:03.000 --> 00:58:06.000
a real tool for working with employees

00:58:06.000 --> 00:58:09.000
and increasing their loyalty and involvement in business appears.

00:58:09.000 --> 00:58:12.000
There is also a very important

00:58:12.000 --> 00:58:15.000
transition of the personnel service

00:58:15.000 --> 00:58:18.000
to a different quality level of development.

00:58:18.000 --> 00:58:21.000
Thus, both the organization

00:58:21.000 --> 00:58:24.000
and the personnel service

00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:27.000
as a guide and an agent of such changes win.

00:58:27.000 --> 00:58:30.000
Let's pay attention to the next slide

00:58:30.000 --> 00:58:33.000
where the cycle of corporate training

00:58:33.000 --> 00:58:36.000
or training system is presented.

00:58:36.000 --> 00:58:39.000
We will touch on this issue again

00:58:39.000 --> 00:58:42.000
in our today's topic

00:58:42.000 --> 00:58:45.000
– the competence model.

00:58:45.000 --> 00:58:48.000
Very often, we have to develop

00:58:48.000 --> 00:58:51.000
the training system.

00:58:51.000 --> 00:58:54.000
The first step is to analyze

00:58:54.000 --> 00:58:57.000
the needs of the employees.

00:58:57.000 --> 00:59:00.000
There are many methods of analysis of needs.

00:59:00.000 --> 00:59:03.000
One of them is the assessment of competence.

00:59:03.000 --> 00:59:06.000
As a result, you often see

00:59:06.000 --> 00:59:09.000
HR and personnel specialists

00:59:09.000 --> 00:59:12.000
making a conspiracy to assess competence.

00:59:12.000 --> 00:59:15.000
We also have to develop the competence model.

00:59:15.000 --> 00:59:18.000
Then they either start the big way

00:59:18.000 --> 00:59:21.000
we are talking about today

00:59:21.000 --> 00:59:24.000
or they use some other methods.

00:59:24.000 --> 00:59:27.000
In fact, the most valid and objective

00:59:27.000 --> 00:59:30.000
is the assessment of competence.

00:59:30.000 --> 00:59:33.000
If we have this competence,

00:59:33.000 --> 00:59:36.000
we can easily make this step.

00:59:36.000 --> 00:59:39.000
All the needs of the training

00:59:39.000 --> 00:59:42.000
become clear and obvious

00:59:42.000 --> 00:59:45.000
and we can work with them.

00:59:45.000 --> 00:59:48.000
The next element of the system

00:59:48.000 --> 00:59:51.000
is the planning of the training.

00:59:51.000 --> 00:59:54.000
We need to understand who, how and when we will be teaching.

00:59:54.000 --> 00:59:57.000
The next step is to develop the program

00:59:57.000 --> 01:00:00.000
and how we will develop the competence.

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:03.000
The next step is to develop the training.

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:06.000
The next step is to assess the effectiveness.

01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:09.000
The assessment of the effectiveness

01:00:09.000 --> 01:00:12.000
is the final element of the system.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:15.000
Let's recall the methods

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:18.000
for assessing the effectiveness of the training.

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:21.000
When we talk about the assessment of the effectiveness

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:24.000
we often mention the name

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:27.000
of Donald Kirkpatrick

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:30.000
who 30 years ago proposed

01:00:30.000 --> 01:00:33.000
the technology of assessing the effectiveness of the training.

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:36.000
Now we know it as the Kirkpatrick model

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:39.000
or the 4-level model.

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:42.000
What is its essence?

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:45.000
Let's recall.

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:48.000
When we talk about the assessment of the effectiveness

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:51.000
of the training or some training program

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:54.000
we should ask ourselves what we assess.

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:57.000
Do we assess the training

01:00:57.000 --> 01:01:00.000
which lasted for 16 hours?

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:03.000
Or do we assess the coach

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:06.000
or the participants?

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:09.000
We always ask this question.

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:12.000
Our task is not to assess the program

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:15.000
but to assess the changes

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:18.000
that the training has brought.

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:21.000
The changes in the work of the participants

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:24.000
should have led to the goal

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:27.000
for which the training program was conceived.

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:30.000
Kirkpatrick proposed to do the following.

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:33.000
First, he said

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:36.000
to assess the reaction of the students

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:39.000
i.e. emotions.

01:01:39.000 --> 01:01:42.000
After the seminar, let's ask

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:45.000
how the participants felt.

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:48.000
Did they like the program?

01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:51.000
Did they feel the heat?

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:54.000
Did they feel cold?

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:57.000
Did they have a proper lunch?

01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:00.000
This is an assessment of emotions.

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:03.000
Let's take a look at the sports.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:06.000
We can listen to a lecture

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:09.000
of a great football coach

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:12.000
and we can say that it was great.

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:15.000
We spent 2-3 hours with such a positive feeling.

01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:18.000
We say that it was great.

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:21.000
It is an emotion.

01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:24.000
We need to understand

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:27.000
what is left in the participants' heads.

01:02:27.000 --> 01:02:30.000
We remember our football lecture.

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:33.000
Do we remember the main rules?

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:36.000
Or is there some inner feeling

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:39.000
about a well-spent time?

01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:42.000
If the football lecture can be like this,

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:45.000
it should not be like this.

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:48.000
Our next task is to understand

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:51.000
what knowledge is left in the participants' heads.

01:02:51.000 --> 01:02:54.000
If we taught operators of the call center

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:57.000
to work effectively, we need to understand

01:02:57.000 --> 01:03:00.000
that they liked everything.

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:03.000
They left with the feeling

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:06.000
that they had a great time.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:09.000
This was not the goal.

01:03:09.000 --> 01:03:12.000
The next level is that there is not enough knowledge.

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:15.000
We can play football,

01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:18.000
but none of us will ever go out on the pitch.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:21.000
We can work with objections.

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:24.000
A manager can sigh a lot

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:27.000
and say that he has been through a lot of trainings

01:03:27.000 --> 01:03:30.000
and he will go back to the same place.

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:33.000
But knowledge does not always imply skill.

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:36.000
We know how to do it.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:39.000
We can work with people.

01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:42.000
The next level is the level of behavior.

01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:45.000
How much behavior has changed

01:03:45.000 --> 01:03:48.000
after the training.

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:51.000
What is behavior? It is competence.

01:03:51.000 --> 01:03:54.000
We understand that this is the most fixed change

01:03:54.000 --> 01:03:57.000
in the development of competence

01:03:57.000 --> 01:04:00.000
that we can analyze.

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:03.000
Has there been a change?

01:04:03.000 --> 01:04:06.000
No.

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:09.000
It is easier for those companies

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:12.000
that have competence models

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:15.000
to reach the third level of efficiency.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:18.000
We have all the tools.

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:21.000
We developed, we conducted

01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:24.000
assessment centers, we evaluated, we looked.

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:27.000
We saw what was at the entrance.

01:04:27.000 --> 01:04:30.000
After repeating the procedures,

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:33.000
we can analyze if there are any changes.

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:36.000
Can we make changes to the training program

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:39.000
that we conducted?

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:42.000
The next point is

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:45.000
how the fourth level of efficiency

01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:48.000
and the business results

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:51.000
led to new behavior.

01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:54.000
The operators of our call center

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:57.000
that we trained and liked

01:04:57.000 --> 01:05:00.000
started to serve the client better.

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:03.000
What did it lead to?

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:06.000
It led to more clients.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:09.000
Clients became more satisfied with our call center.

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:12.000
This is a business result

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:15.000
that we record and that is a consequence

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:18.000
of competence development.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:21.000
To conclude the topic of competence use

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:24.000
in the development of staff,

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:27.000
the company receives the competence

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:30.000
from the employees.

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:33.000
In those companies where the staff

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:36.000
uses competence to form the system

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:39.000
of training and development of employees,

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:42.000
the employees themselves clearly understand

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:45.000
what competence is necessary for their career growth.

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:48.000
They understand what they need to do

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:51.000
to make their work evaluated positively.

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:54.000
The managers have a clear idea

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:57.000
of what their employees were trained for.

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:00.000
They clearly understand

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:03.000
what they can demand from their employees.

01:06:03.000 --> 01:06:06.000
The staff receives a good tool

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:09.000
to evaluate the effectiveness of the investments

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:12.000
that are invested in training.

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:15.000
Let's talk about the use of competence

01:06:15.000 --> 01:06:18.000
in the selection of staff.

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:21.000
We can evaluate the competence

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:24.000
of a certain employee in 40 minutes,

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:27.000
an hour, or an hour and a half.

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:30.000
We have a limited time.

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:33.000
We didn't know anything about the employee before.

01:06:33.000 --> 01:06:36.000
There is no history of our relations.

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:39.000
The evaluation should be as accurate as possible.

01:06:39.000 --> 01:06:42.000
We should make every effort

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:45.000
not to make a mistake.

01:06:45.000 --> 01:06:48.000
The most important thing

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:51.000
is the direct costs and costs

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:54.000
that our company is incurring.

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:57.000
The selection of employees is the most accurate

01:06:57.000 --> 01:07:00.000
if we evaluate them by competence.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:03.000
There are two main methods

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:06.000
that we use.

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:09.000
The first is the interview by competence.

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:12.000
The second is the evaluation centers.

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:15.000
The advantage of the interview by competence

01:07:15.000 --> 01:07:18.000
is that our questions will be based

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:21.000
on the analysis of the work

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:24.000
and will be aimed at the development of the skills

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:27.000
that are required for the work

01:07:27.000 --> 01:07:30.000
that our candidate is applying for.

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:33.000
The next advantage is that the information

01:07:33.000 --> 01:07:36.000
received during the interview

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:39.000
will be easier to structure

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:42.000
and we will easily assign the level of development

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:45.000
that the employee demonstrates,

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:48.000
the information that we will gather

01:07:48.000 --> 01:07:51.000
during the interview,

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:54.000
and the skills that are required for the job.

01:07:54.000 --> 01:07:57.000
Unfortunately, there are disadvantages.

01:07:57.000 --> 01:08:00.000
The first one is the long duration of the interview.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:03.000
In this case, it is important to use

01:08:03.000 --> 01:08:06.000
the tool that we talked about today,

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:09.000
which is the tool of a pair comparison.

